SIMPLE_SHELL(1)                    User Commands                   SIMPLE_SHELL(1)

NAME
       simple_shell - A simple shell implementation

SYNOPSIS
       ./shell

DESCRIPTION
       simple_shell is a basic shell implementation that provides command
       execution capabilities similar to bash or sh.

       The shell supports:
       - Basic command execution
       - Built-in commands (exit, env)
       - PATH environment variable handling
       - Signal handling (Ctrl+C)
       - Error handling and reporting

BUILT-IN COMMANDS
       exit    Exits the shell
       env     Displays environment variables

EXAMPLES
       ./shell
              Start the shell in interactive mode

       echo "ls" | ./shell
              Execute a single command and exit

AUTHORS
       Written by Joshua and Mohamed

BUGS
       Report bugs to the project repository

SEE ALSO
       bash(1), sh(1)

